        h2: 'What homeowners look for before choosing a roofer',
        body: `Before a homeowner calls a roofer, they\'ve already done 20 minutes of research. They\'ve looked at your reviews, checked if you\'re licensed and insured, scanned your photo gallery, and looked for red flags. A weak website with stock photos and no verifiable credentials loses that prospect before contact is ever made.\n\nThe roofing websites that win display real project photos, video testimonials, certifications from manufacturers like GAF or Owens Corning, and a clear service area map. Homeowners want to see that you\'ve done exactly their type of roof in their neighborhood.`,
