        body: `The most common mistake small agencies make is positioning themselves as a full-service shop for any business. That sounds like more opportunity — but it makes you forgettable. Prospects can\'t tell why you\'re different from the 50 other agencies in their Google results.\n\nThe most effective agencies niche down: "We do paid ads for home service companies" or "We handle social media for restaurants." A clear niche lets you speak directly to a prospect\'s specific problems, command higher rates, and build case studies that resonate. Your website should lead with this positioning, not bury it.`,
